Darolutamide can act as a progesterone receptor (PR) antagonist in the laboratory setting with approximately 1% activity when compared to its actions at the androgen receptor. The clinical relevance is not known at this time.[L10872] ', 'Darolutamide, through its downstream effects on cancer cell growth, treats castrate-resistant prostate cancer. It inhibits cancer cell growth and markedly lowers prostate specific antigen (PSA) levels through potent androgen receptor antagonism.[A189060,A189063,L10872]', 'DrugBank', 0, 0, 0);
